$MAIL is point to /var/spool/mail/john
set $MAIL on .bashrc
export MAIL=/var/spool/mail/$USER
and qq mail is /var/spool/mail/john/qq/INBOX/cur new tmp


offlineimap is too dangerous!

pamcan -S mpop
man mpop 
"delivery maildir directory
                     Deliver the mails to the given maildir  directory.  The  directory
                     must  exist  and it must have the maildir subdirectories cur, new,
                     and tmp; mpop will not create directories. This delivery type only
                     works on file systems that support hard links.
"
you have to create those directories  mkdir /var/spool/mail/john/qq/INBOX/new cur tmp

crontab -e
*/15 * * * * mpop

about maildir and mbox, mbox is just one file, and maildir is a directory

those are maildir
INBOX/new cur tmp
Sent/
Trash/

$MAIL/qq/INBOX/new cur tmp       /var/spool/mail/john/qq/INBOX/new cur tmp
$MAIL/qq/Sent

about mutt read html pdf

pacman -S xdg-utils w3m
pacman -S antiword odt2txt sxiv 
pacman -S bash-completion
vim ~/.mailcap
application/msword; antiword %s|uniq; copiousoutput
application/pdf; pdftotext -enc UTF-8 %s /dev/stdout; copiousoutput
application/vnd.oasis.opendocument.text; odt2txt %s|uniq; copiousoutput
image/*; sxiv %s; test=test -n "$DISPLAY"
text/html; w3m -dump -ppc 9 -I %{charset} -T text/html %s|uniq; copiousoutput

